==English==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[herculean]]
===Etymology===
see [[Hercules]]
===Pronunciation===
(US) IPA: /hərˈkjuːliən/

===Adjective===
'''Herculean'''
# very [[strong]], similar to the mythical [[Hercules]] in size
#:* '''1607''': But this is not the best:--look, pr'ythee, Charmian, / How this '''Herculean''' Roman does become / The carriage of his chafe. — [[Shakespeare]], ''[http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Tragedy_of_Antony_and_Cleopatra Antony and Cleopatra], i 3''
# said of something that will take a huge amount of [[work]] -- a ''Herculean labour'', a ''Herculean task''
#*'''1748,''' Tobias George Smollett, ''The Adventures of Roderick Random''
#*:He replied in a dry manner, that I would find it a '''Herculean''' task to chastise everybody who should laugh at my expense;

